Converting between linear combinations and coordinate vectors, 
\begin_inset Formula $\left[\begin{array}{c}
2\\
7\\
-3
\end{array}\right]_{\mathcal{C}}$
\end_inset

 
\shape italic
means
\shape default
 
\begin_inset Formula $2$
\end_inset

 times the first vector of 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{C}$
\end_inset

 plus 
\begin_inset Formula $7$
\end_inset

 times the second vector of 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{C}$
\end_inset

 minus 3 times the third vector of 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{C}$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $2\left[\begin{array}{c}
1\\
0\\
0
\end{array}\right]_{\mathcal{E}}+7\left[\begin{array}{c}
1\\
1\\
0
\end{array}\right]_{\mathcal{E}}-3\left[\begin{array}{c}
1\\
1\\
1
\end{array}\right]_{\mathcal{E}}$
\end_inset

.
 On the other hand 
\begin_inset Formula $6I_{:,1}+4I_{:,2}-3I_{:,3}$
\end_inset

 
\shape italic
is
\shape default
 
\begin_inset Formula $6$
\end_inset

 times the first vector of 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{E}$
\end_inset

 plus 
\begin_inset Formula $4$
\end_inset

 times the second vector of 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{E}$
\end_inset

 minus 
\begin_inset Formula $3$
\end_inset

 times the third vector of 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{E}$
\end_inset

, the precise meaning of 
\begin_inset Formula $\left[\begin{array}{c}
6\\
4\\
-3
\end{array}\right]_{\mathcal{E}}$
\end_inset

.
 In full detail,
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
\left[\begin{array}{c}
2\\
7\\
-3
\end{array}\right]_{\mathcal{C}} & =2\left[\begin{array}{c}
1\\
0\\
0
\end{array}\right]_{\mathcal{E}}+7\left[\begin{array}{c}
1\\
1\\
0
\end{array}\right]_{\mathcal{E}}-3\left[\begin{array}{c}
1\\
1\\
1
\end{array}\right]_{\mathcal{E}}\\
 & =2I_{:,1}+7(I_{:,1}+I_{:2})-3(I_{:,1}+I_{:,2}+I_{:,3})\\
 & =(2+7-3)I_{:,1}+(7-3)I_{:,2}-3I_{:,3}\\
 & =6I_{:,1}+4I_{:,2}-3I_{:,3}=\left[\begin{array}{c}
6\\
4\\
-3
\end{array}\right]_{\mathcal{E}}\\
\left[\begin{array}{c}
4\\
6\\
-3
\end{array}\right]_{\mathcal{B}} & =4I_{:,2}+6I_{:,1}-3I_{:,3}=6I_{:,1}+4I_{:,2}-3I_{:,3}=\left[\begin{array}{c}
6\\
4\\
-3
\end{array}\right]_{\mathcal{E}}
\end{align*}

\end_inset


